"title": "5337: hiring",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5337",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Laws relating to hiring</h2>\n<h3>Hired workers must be paid on time</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:13\">LEV 19:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:14-Deut24:15\">DEU 24:14–24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Regular rates of pay must be established</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:50\">LEV 25:50</a></p>\n<h3>Hired workers are to be treated with kindness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:6\">LEV 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:40\">LEV 25:39–25:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:53\">LEV 25:53</a></p>\n<h3>Hired foreigners were excluded from the Passover</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:43-Exod12:45\">EXO 12:43–12:45</a></p>\n<h3>Hired workers must be carefully chosen</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:10\">PRO 26:10</a></p>\n<h3>Loss of a hired animal is covered by the price</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:15\">EXO 22:15</a></p>\n<h2>Various kinds of hiring</h2>\n<h3>A hired husband</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:16\">GEN 30:16</a></p>\n<h3>A hired prophet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:4\">DEU 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:12-Neh6:13\">NEH 6:12–6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:2\">NEH 13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:11\">JUD 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>A hired priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:10\">JDG 17:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:4\">JDG 18:4</a></p>\n<h3>Hired soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:4\">JDG 9:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:6\">2KI 7:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6-1Chr19:7\">1CH 19:6–19:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:6\">2CH 25:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:21\">JER 46:21</a> <em>No hired mercenary army was ever approved by the LORD (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:7-2Chr25:10\">2Ch 25:7–10</a>).</em></p>\n<h3>Other hirings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:5\">1SA 2:5</a> <em>hirings for food</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:12\">2CH 24:12</a> <em>masons and carpenters</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:5\">EZR 4:5</a> <em>counsellors</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:20\">ISA 7:20</a> <em>a razor, symbolising the judgment to be brought by the king of Assyria</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:17\">ISA 23:17</a> <em>prostitutes</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:6\">ISA 46:6</a> <em>goldsmiths</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:20\">MRK 1:20</a> <em>fishermen</em></p>\n<h2>Teachings illustrated by hired workers</h2>\n<h3>The brevity and hardness of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:1-Job7:3\">JOB 7:1–7:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:6\">JOB 14:6</a></p>\n<h3>Christian workers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:15\">MAT 20:1–20:15</a></strong> <em>This parable teaches that believers should not serve in a mercenary spirit but recognise that God's reward is based upon grace.</em></p>\n<h3>The severity of the world and the kindness of God</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:15-Luke15:19\">LUK 15:15–15:19</a></p>\n<h2>The difference between hired and good shepherds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11-John10:13\">JHN 10:11–10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>",
